article.headline: Cummins' 16 lead Colgate past Army 74-55

images.name: Army Black Knights vs. Colgate Raiders: Full Highlights
images.caption: Army Black Knights vs. Colgate Raiders: Full Highlights

article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- — Brady Cummins had 16 points in Colgate's 74-55 victory over Army on Wednesday night. Cummins was 6 of 11 shooting (4 for 7 from 3-point range) for the Raiders (14-8, 8-1 Patriot League). Braeden Smith scored 13 points while shooting 5 for 11, including 3 for 7 from beyond the arc, and added five assists and six steals. Ryan Moffatt was 5 of 7 shooting (1 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 11 points. The Raiders picked up their sixth straight win. The Black Knights (6-16, 2-7) were led in scoring by Josh Scovens, who finished with 17 points. Abe Johnson added nine points and eight rebounds for Army. In addition, TJ Small finished with nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
